                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18200217-91-off517 t18200217-91-crimeloc521"></join>. I found a pressure on me behind, put my hand round, and my handkerchief was put into it - it did not drop from my pocket. I turned round, and saw the prisoner in custody.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18200217-91-person981">
                  GEORGE 
                  MOSS
               <interp inst="t18200217-91-person981" type="surname" value="MOSS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200217-91-person981" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200217-91-person981" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a clerk in the Post Office. I observed a boy following Mr. Knox, and looking at his handkerchief, which was about two inches out of his pocket. The prisoner came up Chiswell-street, joined him, and drew the handkerchief out. I seized him, and he immediately dropped the handkerchief. Mr. Knox caught it as it fell.</p>
